issue.title: Concurrency fixes
issue.body: As discussed on the lsp4e-dev mailing list, these are some fixes we made internally to try and address some weird behaviour we used to get, particularly under load. The existing implementation submits document update events to a thread pool where they may get scheduled in any order. This can cause the client's and server's view of the state of a document to diverge, resulting in phantom error markers and so on.

comment.body:
Also, I'm curious: how likely is it that the document listener receives events in the wrong order? I know that starting many futures is likely to cause them in the wrong order, but where they "created" in the right order? If yes, we may not need to deal too much with timestamps, and can just trust the `.then...` methods on Future to run things in the same order as events are received.
Did you find a case where events got received in the wrong order? as document edition is usually sequential, I'd be a bit surprised.

commits.message:
Enable Vectorization for supported ops on Z

This commit enables vectorization of following operations in Vector API
for different species.

1. Vector Load and Store for all species.
2. Binary Operations
   1. Add/Subtraction : Enabled for all species
   2. Multiplication : Enabled for all species except Long
   3. Division : Enabled for Float and Doubles only
   4. AND/OR/XOR : Enables for all integral types
3. NEG operation for all species
4. Broadcast operation for all species

Signed-off-by: Rahil Shah <rahil@ca.ibm.com>

Add Env option to disable merging of guards

On X and Z right now to get the vectorAPIExpansion to vectorize or
scalarize the operation, we need to disable OSRGuard merging. Change in
this commit will allow developers on Z and X to test vector API
expansion by disabling merging of OSR guards using environment variable.

Signed-off-by: Rahil Shah <rahil@ca.ibm.com>

Merge pull request #6517 from r30shah/0.33VectorAPIPR
